Rapper and choreographer Tumi Tladi (29)'s sudden death has shocked the music industry. It was announced today on social media by some of his close friends. The Basadi-hitmaker was the son of celebrated jazz music promoter and businessman Peter Tladi. His cause of death had not yet been announced. So far, many of his fellow industry friends such as AKA and Slikouronlife have already paid their tributes to the young rapper. Tumi released his latest single titled Presidential featuring Nadia Nakai and Mustbedubz over a week ago. This is a developing story… Rest in Peace my boy. ?? pic.twitter.com/mny240Ax7b Rest In Power @Tumitladi ??‍?? https://t.co/VqIAOsJPQw  ABOUT TUMI TLADI 